0. Requirements:

    0.1 - Java - OpenJDK (recommended, but all Sun-Compatible JVMs should work).
        >= Latest 1.6, 64-bit

    0.2 - Simple Build Tool (sbt: http://code.google.com/p/simple-build-tool/)
        >= 0.7.4

    0.3 - Scala (will be downloaded by sbt automatically)
        >= 2.8.1
        
    0.4 - ZSH Shell (for SvdSystemManager)
        >= 4.3.10
        
    0.5 - Sudo (for SvdSystemManager)
        >= 1.7.4p6
    
    0.6 - Sigar library (for SvdSystemManager)
        >= 1.6.3.82
        
    0.7 - Smack library (for XMPP Notifications)
        >= 3.0.4

    0.8 - pIRCbot library (for IRC Notifications)
        >= 1.4.2
        
    0.9 - mongo database (for SvdDB, mongodb: http://mongodb.org)
        >= 1.6.5-x86_64
        
    0.10 - List of currently supported platforms:
        Mac OSX (100% features, development),
        Free BSD (100% features, production),



1. Instalation
    1.1 - install native libraries from "libs.native.64" folder (currently only 64bit systems are fully supported)
        In FreeBSD 8.1:
            A. Become superuser (root):
                * sudo -i
            B. Install ports:
                * portsnap fetch
                * portsnap extract
            C. Install OpenJDK6 (OpenJDK7 will be supported parallely)
                * unset JAVA_HOME
                * cd /usr/ports/java/openjdk6 && make install
                * follow requirements and instructions
    1.2 - sbt "project SvdMaintainer" run



2. Testing
    2.1 - Use sbt test

That's all folks



